Founded in October 1988 by Mosholu Preservation Corporation (MPC), a not-for-profit affiliate of Montefiore Medical Center, the Norwood News is a bi-weekly newspaper that primarily serves the Northwest Bronx neighborhoods of Norwood, Bedford Park, Fordham and University Heights. It has won numerous awards, including the New York Press Club award for community coverage. Its current Editor-in-chief, David Cruz, has been with the newspaper since 2013.
